# PlatformIO libraries

Each library exposes public headers only through its own `src/` directory and
declares its direct dependencies in `library.json`.

| Library | Responsibility |
| --- | --- |
| `fw_app` | Shared feature application context |
| `fw_core` | Shared time, lifecycle, and debug helpers |
| `fw_esp32` | ESP32 clock, restart, and NVS adapters |
| `fw_network` | AP/STA management, reconnects, and scanning |
| `fw_web` | HTTP host, router, and JSON helpers |
| `fw_ota` | ArduinoOTA and HTTP firmware update services |
| `fw_telemetry` | Fixed-capacity telemetry history |
| `cooling_domain` | Platform-independent cooling state machine |
| `cooling_feature` | Cooling hardware, persistence, UI, API, and feature integration |
| `blink_feature` | Minimal status LED feature and framework reuse example |

Framework libraries must not include cooling headers. `cooling_domain` must not
include framework, Arduino, or ESP32 headers.
